    "narrative": "Our strongest play today is **Trevor Story** (75.93), who benefits from a favorable matchup against Arrighetti. Beyond the SP skill advantage, **Story** stands out due to a slow opposing delivery that significantly bolsters his stolen base potential\u2014a critical factor for our strategy. **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.65) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (67.84) also anchor the daily output; **Pasquantino** enjoys a substantial platoon-driven boost against Emerson Hancock, while **Soderstrom** capitalizes on the combination of a high-ceiling order spot and a vulnerable pitcher. While **Corbin Carroll** (63.85) faces a daunting task against the elite Imanaga, his underlying power-speed profile keeps him in the \"Strong\" start tier, even with a penalty for the opponent\u2019s ability to neutralize base stealers.\n\nThe tightest bench decision involves **Jose Caballero**, who missed the cut with a 41.62 score. Despite his high stolen base upside (60%), his projected output was heavily suppressed by a difficult matchup against Bradish and a low-leverage batting position. **Alex Freeland** was similarly considered but ultimately left on the bench as the optimizer prioritized the higher-rated floor provided by **Travis Bazzana**. We are closely monitoring the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Luis Campusano**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Josh Naylor**, **Austin Riley**, **Mickey Moniak**, **James Wood**, and **Vinnie Pasquantino**; specifically, **Mickey Moniak** faces significant risk today, as his projection suffers from a sharp downward adjustment against the elite Chris Sale. We expect volatility across these spots as official lineups are posted, but for now, the efficiency scores suggest we are well-positioned to chase counting stats without over-leveraging our game caps.",
